The Vice President visited the Walter Reed National Military Medical Center in Bethesda, Maryland to recognize National PTSD Awareness Day and express gratitude for the work being done at the Intrepid Center for Excellence. He acknowledged the challenges faced by veterans with post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) and emphasized the importance of addressing the emotional and psychological wounds that they carry home. The Vice President thanked the Senators who have shown leadership on this issue and assured veterans that help is available. He also shared a personal story about his father's struggles with PTSD after the Korean War. The Vice President praised the caregivers at Walter Reed for their dedication and service.